'''Budiná''' ({{lang-hu|Budaszállás}}) is a [[village]] and [[municipality]] in the [[Lučenec District]] in the [[Banská Bystrica Region]] of [[Slovakia]].

==History==
In [[history|historical records]], the village was first mentioned in 1393 (1393 ''Brtolehutaya'', 1467 ''Budalehotha''). It belonged to [[Divín]] castle. From 1554 to 1595 it suffered [[Ottoman Empire|Turkish]] occupation.

